WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.835
[ mouse squeaks ]

00:02.920 --> 00:03.920
[ penguins wenk ]

00:06.507 --> 00:07.507
[ all cheering ]

00:10.677 --> 00:12.094
[ screeches ]

00:13.388 --> 00:14.430
♪ Adventure Time ♪

00:14.515 --> 00:16.474
♪ Come on, grab your friends ♪

00:16.558 --> 00:18.518
♪ We'll go to very
distant lands ♪

00:18.602 --> 00:20.853
♪ with Jake the dog
and Finn the human ♪

00:20.938 --> 00:22.730
♪ the fun will never end ♪

00:22.814 --> 00:24.857
♪ lt's Adventure Time ♪

00:26.000 --> 00:32.073
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:33.325 --> 00:34.575
[ birds chirping ]

00:34.660 --> 00:37.119
Walking, walking,

00:37.204 --> 00:38.955
walking -- hambone break!

00:39.039 --> 00:40.122
Whoo-hoo!

00:40.207 --> 00:41.749
Hey, hey, get away from me.

00:41.833 --> 00:43.626
[ laughing ]

00:43.710 --> 00:45.419
Quit it!
[ laughs ]

00:45.504 --> 00:46.921
MAN:
Food for a beggar?

00:47.005 --> 00:47.797
[ coughs ]

00:47.881 --> 00:49.507
Food for a poor old man?

00:49.591 --> 00:51.259
Geez Louise, guy.

00:51.343 --> 00:53.469
So, you got any, kid?

00:53.554 --> 00:54.929
Food?

00:55.013 --> 00:57.265
l got this little piece of sugar.

00:57.349 --> 00:58.266
[ thinking ]
Nuts.

00:58.350 --> 01:00.101
l'm frickin' all aboutsugar.

01:00.185 --> 01:02.687
But l'm even more all about feeding hobos!

01:02.771 --> 01:03.688
JAKE:
Wait, Finn.

01:03.772 --> 01:04.938
Maybe helping this starving

01:05.022 --> 01:06.566
homeless guy is the wrong thing to do.

01:06.650 --> 01:07.441
Why?

01:07.526 --> 01:08.526
l don't know.

01:08.610 --> 01:09.527
l-I said "Maybe."

01:09.611 --> 01:12.280
A hero always helps someone in need.

01:12.364 --> 01:16.117
And besides, he's probably
secretly an elf who will reward

01:16.201 --> 01:17.410
us for being nice.

01:17.494 --> 01:19.078
Here you go, buddy.

01:19.162 --> 01:20.162
Whoa!

01:20.247 --> 01:22.290
[ chewing ]

01:22.374 --> 01:26.627
You know, believe it or not,
l'm not reallya beggar.

01:26.712 --> 01:28.879
l'm actually a...

01:28.964 --> 01:31.424
♪ Magic Man ♪

01:32.009 --> 01:33.259
Whoa! Ah, yeah!

01:33.343 --> 01:34.719
He's -- he's magic!

01:34.803 --> 01:36.596
l didn't --
l didn't expect this.

01:36.680 --> 01:39.223
[ whistling ]

01:39.308 --> 01:40.725
[ bird chirping ]

01:43.395 --> 01:45.479
Magic!

01:45.564 --> 01:47.315
Away!

01:47.399 --> 01:49.191
[ flapping, squishing ]

01:49.276 --> 01:50.860
Think happy thoughts --

01:50.944 --> 01:53.446
Little, cute bees, little babies,
tiny, tiny bunnies.

01:53.530 --> 01:55.615
What is wrong with you,
Magic Man?!

01:55.699 --> 01:57.450
You gave me that candy.

01:57.534 --> 02:02.330
Now l'll do you a favor in return --
a magic favor!

02:02.414 --> 02:05.207
♪ A mystical, magical favor ♪

02:05.292 --> 02:06.375
Whoa! Wha-- ugh!

02:06.460 --> 02:07.293
[ screams ]

02:07.377 --> 02:08.377
Whoa, dude!

02:08.461 --> 02:10.045
♪ For you ♪

02:10.130 --> 02:11.422
Why'd you do that?!

02:11.506 --> 02:15.009
Because this day, a magical
life lesson comes to you.

02:15.093 --> 02:16.510
No, change me back!

02:16.595 --> 02:19.597
Not until you appreciate what a jerk l am.

02:19.681 --> 02:20.514
Wazoo!

02:23.435 --> 02:24.644
What a nutty guy.

02:24.728 --> 02:26.020
What the heck, man?!

02:26.104 --> 02:27.355
What kind of deal is that?!

02:27.439 --> 02:29.649
l help somebody out,
and they make me a stinky foot?!

02:29.733 --> 02:30.524
[ sniffs ]

02:30.609 --> 02:31.525
You smell pretty good.

02:31.610 --> 02:32.777
Get off of me, man!

02:32.861 --> 02:34.070
l can't be a hero if I'm a big,

02:34.154 --> 02:34.945
good-smelling foot!

02:35.030 --> 02:37.990
Maybe you're looking at
this magic gift all wrong.

02:38.075 --> 02:39.992
Now that you're a huge foot,

02:40.077 --> 02:43.037
you can kick evil's butt, like,
way more times as hard.

02:43.121 --> 02:44.288
You're 100% kick, man!

02:44.373 --> 02:45.790
Why are you being so

02:45.874 --> 02:47.124
level-headed about this?

02:47.209 --> 02:48.709
Don't be a siss, Finn.

02:48.794 --> 02:50.211
Here, come on, kick my butt.

02:50.295 --> 02:53.047
You're the siss, siss!

02:53.131 --> 02:54.131
Hah! Agh!

02:54.216 --> 02:56.092
Ouch! Ooh, ouch!

02:56.176 --> 02:56.967
See, man?

02:57.052 --> 02:58.803
Let's give your foot body a shot.

02:58.887 --> 02:59.804
No, dude!

02:59.888 --> 03:02.807
l want to go find that
Magic Man and get my body back!

03:02.891 --> 03:04.517
Shh! Shh! Shh! Shh!

03:04.601 --> 03:07.353
Just be a foot for a little bit.

03:07.437 --> 03:08.604
[ as Finn ]
Okay, I will.

03:08.689 --> 03:10.064
[ as himself ]
Awesome, dude.

03:10.148 --> 03:11.899
You'll never regret this.

03:11.983 --> 03:12.817
[ laughs ]

03:12.901 --> 03:16.112
Okay, when the next monster comes
along, he'll step on that

03:16.196 --> 03:17.905
trigger over there, sending your

03:17.989 --> 03:20.700
giant foot body into the
monster's crotch!

03:20.784 --> 03:22.410
This sucks, dude.

03:22.494 --> 03:23.411
Shh!

03:23.495 --> 03:25.955
[ roaring ]

03:26.039 --> 03:27.248
We're evil!

03:27.332 --> 03:28.249
[ roars ]

03:28.333 --> 03:29.291
[ both shout ]

03:29.376 --> 03:33.295
Our crotch --
our evil crotch!

03:33.380 --> 03:34.338
[ laughs ]

03:34.423 --> 03:35.339
What'd l tell you?

03:35.424 --> 03:36.424
You're a great hero!

03:36.508 --> 03:38.092
Let's go set up some more crotch

03:38.176 --> 03:40.344
catapults so we can laugh
and be heroes.

03:40.429 --> 03:41.429
No, Jake.

03:41.513 --> 03:42.805
Let's find that Magic Man.

03:42.889 --> 03:44.515
Finn, being an enormous

03:44.599 --> 03:46.100
crotch-kicking foot is a gift.

03:46.184 --> 03:47.351
Don't scorn a gift.

03:47.436 --> 03:48.769
[ indistinct shouting ]

03:48.854 --> 03:49.729
Town on fire!

03:49.813 --> 03:51.564
This looks like a job for foot

03:51.648 --> 03:52.815
Finn stomping ability!

03:52.899 --> 03:54.525
But l-l can't even bend

03:54.609 --> 03:55.776
these big, fat toes, man.

03:55.861 --> 03:57.194
You can do it, Finn.

03:57.279 --> 03:58.738
What'd l teach you, dude?

03:58.822 --> 04:00.865
Not to scorn the

04:00.949 --> 04:03.117
kicking of people in the crotch?

04:03.201 --> 04:04.452
You got it!

04:04.536 --> 04:06.370
Now l'm gonna go rescue all the

04:06.455 --> 04:09.749
babies in town --
only the babies.

04:09.833 --> 04:11.375
Get your hero on, dude!

04:11.460 --> 04:12.543
Aaaah!

04:12.627 --> 04:13.836
[ indistinct shouting ]

04:13.920 --> 04:14.754
Unh!

04:14.838 --> 04:16.797
Okay, you can do this, Finn.

04:16.882 --> 04:18.173
Start small, man.

04:18.257 --> 04:20.301
l'm taking you down!

04:20.385 --> 04:22.636
[ grunting ]

04:22.721 --> 04:23.554
lt's hot!

04:23.638 --> 04:25.264
Oh, man, l'm smoking hot!

04:25.348 --> 04:26.348
Please, help me out!

04:26.433 --> 04:27.266
l can't move!

04:27.350 --> 04:29.351
lt's another one of those freaks!

04:29.436 --> 04:30.978
He probably startedthis fire!

04:31.062 --> 04:32.646
No, I didn't start any --

04:32.731 --> 04:34.899
Throw him under the bridge
with the others!

04:34.983 --> 04:36.400
ALL:
Get rid of the freak!

04:36.485 --> 04:38.068
[ chanting ]
Freak! Freak!

04:38.153 --> 04:40.237
Stay out of our town, freak!

04:40.322 --> 04:41.238
Unh!

04:41.323 --> 04:42.114
[ sighs ]

04:42.199 --> 04:43.032
[ sniffles ]

04:43.116 --> 04:44.700
l'm not a freak. l'm a hero.

04:44.785 --> 04:45.618
JAKE:
Finn!

04:45.702 --> 04:47.244
Jake, how'd you find me?

04:47.329 --> 04:49.497
Oh, l can sense when
you're about to cry.

04:49.581 --> 04:51.165
lt's like a mother/daughter thing.

04:51.249 --> 04:52.625
l'm not gonna cry, man!

04:52.709 --> 04:53.918
l just feellike crying.

04:54.002 --> 04:56.796
We have to find that magic guy
and get my body back now!

04:56.880 --> 05:00.049
What we haveto do is find out
what reeks under this bridge.

05:00.133 --> 05:01.675
[ sniffs ]
- Jake!

05:01.760 --> 05:04.094
Ew, it's blocking out your good foot smell.

05:04.179 --> 05:05.221
Get back here!

05:05.305 --> 05:08.390
Ugh, it -- it smells
like vomit on fire.

05:08.475 --> 05:11.560
lt's like fancy cheese
in an old guy's mouth.

05:11.645 --> 05:12.478
Welcome, travelers.

05:12.562 --> 05:13.354
Aah!

05:13.438 --> 05:15.856
l am Gork, leader of Freak City.

05:15.941 --> 05:19.026
Ah, l can see one of you has
felt the Magic Man's touch.

05:19.110 --> 05:19.944
Yeah.

05:20.028 --> 05:21.070
You know that guy?

05:21.154 --> 05:23.197
l will tell you all that I know.

05:23.281 --> 05:24.824
[ vomits ]

05:24.908 --> 05:26.826
We are the accursed ones,

05:26.910 --> 05:31.288
all once normal guys and gals who
crossed paths with the Magic Man.

05:31.373 --> 05:32.832
That's Zap, The Arm.

05:32.916 --> 05:34.166
[ mumbles ]

05:34.251 --> 05:35.835
Trudy, The Waist.

05:35.919 --> 05:37.086
[ coughs ]

05:37.170 --> 05:39.421
That's Wee Wee and Gorflax.

05:39.506 --> 05:41.549
They were turned into tonsils.

05:41.633 --> 05:42.758
And that's Kim.

05:42.843 --> 05:43.843
[ chuckles ]

05:43.927 --> 05:45.553
[ smooching ]

05:45.637 --> 05:47.221
But, please, make yourselves at home.

05:47.305 --> 05:48.722
Would you like something to drink?

05:48.807 --> 05:50.391
Do you have any orange juice?

05:50.475 --> 05:51.684
No.

05:51.768 --> 05:53.519
Well, uh, l don't know.

05:53.603 --> 05:55.604
Maybe. Uh, l don't think so.

05:55.689 --> 05:56.522
l'll go check.

05:56.606 --> 05:59.775
Yo, Finn, this place is
really bumming me out.

05:59.860 --> 06:00.943
Let's get out of here.

06:01.027 --> 06:02.278
What?! No, dude.

06:02.362 --> 06:05.239
These guys might be my only
hope of finding the Magic Man.

06:05.323 --> 06:07.449
Hey, we actually do have orange juice.

06:07.534 --> 06:08.993
Thanks for being cool and all,

06:09.077 --> 06:11.579
but what do you know about this Magic Man?

06:11.663 --> 06:12.830
How do we catch him?

06:12.914 --> 06:14.373
Oh, he can't be caught.

06:14.457 --> 06:15.958
He's got magic.

06:16.042 --> 06:17.543
And we're worthless freaks.

06:17.627 --> 06:18.919
We can't ever beat him.

06:19.004 --> 06:21.922
So we've gathered here
to wallow in our self-pity.

06:22.007 --> 06:24.341
But don't y'all even want to try?

06:24.426 --> 06:25.217
Eh, no.

06:25.302 --> 06:26.260
Why not?

06:26.344 --> 06:28.345
You're all totally miserable here.

06:28.430 --> 06:29.597
Eh, it's a living.

06:29.681 --> 06:31.140
No, it's not, Zap!

06:31.224 --> 06:32.266
lt's not a living!

06:32.350 --> 06:33.517
lt's dookie diapers!

06:33.602 --> 06:35.019
l don't want to be a foot!

06:35.103 --> 06:37.813
Well, get used to it.

06:37.898 --> 06:38.731
We did.

06:38.815 --> 06:41.358
Yeah, Finn, maybe there's another
lesson to be learned here --

06:41.443 --> 06:46.280
to accept what fate has given you
and stay a miserable foot.

06:46.364 --> 06:50.117
Gork, can we live here in this
pile of trash and rats forever?

06:50.201 --> 06:51.869
Yeah, man. Do it up.

06:51.953 --> 06:52.745
Awesome.

06:52.829 --> 06:54.330
[ rats squeaking ]
Here we go.

06:54.414 --> 06:56.081
Jake, stop screwing around.

06:56.166 --> 06:58.083
You're gonna make me give into depression.

06:58.168 --> 07:00.169
Eh, what are you gonna do about it?

07:00.253 --> 07:01.420
Probably nothing, right?

07:01.504 --> 07:03.464
lf you're depressed, you'll do nothing.

07:03.548 --> 07:05.132
l...

07:05.216 --> 07:06.926
Maybe l will do nothing.

07:07.010 --> 07:09.053
Maybe l'll just lay down here.

07:09.137 --> 07:10.012
[ grunts ]

07:10.096 --> 07:11.138
[ sighs ]

07:11.222 --> 07:14.308
Lay down -- unh --
and rot like the rest of you.

07:14.392 --> 07:15.392
Yeah!

07:15.477 --> 07:17.061
[ chanting ]
Stay a foot!

07:17.145 --> 07:19.939
Stay a foot! Stay a foot!

07:20.023 --> 07:22.483
♪ ls this really my life? ♪

07:22.567 --> 07:24.902
♪ ls this how my story ends? ♪

07:24.986 --> 07:29.406
♪ Being in this body seems
like a battle that l cannot win ♪

07:29.491 --> 07:31.533
♪ Maybe l should lay my head down slow ♪

07:31.618 --> 07:34.954
♪ And sleep until it's all over ♪

07:35.038 --> 07:36.956
♪ ls this the end ♪

07:37.040 --> 07:39.500
♪ Of the hero boy named Finn? ♪

07:39.584 --> 07:40.501
♪ Heck no! ♪

07:40.585 --> 07:41.877
♪ Darn heck no! ♪

07:41.962 --> 07:43.921
♪ This isn't how I go ♪

07:44.005 --> 07:45.089
♪ l'm gonna kill it ♪

07:45.173 --> 07:46.507
♪ l'm gonna kick life's butt ♪

07:46.591 --> 07:47.633
♪ And win it ♪

07:47.717 --> 07:48.509
♪ To win it ♪

07:48.593 --> 07:50.219
♪ l'm gonna take life's name ♪

07:50.303 --> 07:51.095
[ spits ]

07:51.179 --> 07:52.179
♪ And spit on it ♪

07:52.263 --> 07:53.389
♪ And kick it ♪

07:53.473 --> 07:55.432
♪ Life can just go eat it ♪

07:55.517 --> 07:58.018
♪ 'Cause this is a man's game ♪

07:58.103 --> 07:58.936
Get up, Gork!

07:59.020 --> 07:59.812
Huh? Why?

07:59.896 --> 08:02.106
♪ l'm not gonna let you lie here ♪

08:02.190 --> 08:04.024
♪ And waste away ♪

08:04.109 --> 08:06.485
♪ You better get up, Gork,
or I'll kick you up ♪

08:06.569 --> 08:08.195
♪ Today's the day ♪

08:08.279 --> 08:09.780
Whoa, okay, man.

08:09.864 --> 08:10.823
Just be cool.

08:10.907 --> 08:12.700
♪ And I'm not gonna be cool ♪

08:12.784 --> 08:14.576
♪ 'Cause l'm pipin' hot ♪

08:14.661 --> 08:15.494
Ow!

08:15.578 --> 08:16.370
♪ Get up, Trudy ♪

08:16.454 --> 08:17.246
♪ Get up, Kim ♪

08:17.330 --> 08:18.539
♪ l'm not gonna let you rot ♪

08:18.623 --> 08:19.456
[ rats squeaking ]

08:19.541 --> 08:20.332
Hey, Finn.

08:20.417 --> 08:22.167
♪ Jake ♪

08:22.252 --> 08:24.628
♪ Stop telling me to enjoy ♪

08:24.713 --> 08:26.338
♪ Being a foot ♪

08:26.423 --> 08:28.507
♪ And get out of that trash ♪

08:28.591 --> 08:29.425
[ chuckles ]

08:29.509 --> 08:31.593
l can't take you seriously
when you're singing, man.

08:31.678 --> 08:32.970
♪ Get up ♪
- Aah!

08:33.054 --> 08:35.014
♪ All of you make me sick ♪

08:35.097 --> 08:36.890
♪ l'll fix you with my kicks ♪

08:36.975 --> 08:39.183
♪ Gonna reconstruct y'all's self-worth ♪

08:39.269 --> 08:41.729
♪ Brick by emotional brick ♪

08:41.813 --> 08:42.645
[ all grunting ]

08:42.731 --> 08:43.563
[ grunting ]

08:45.650 --> 08:46.442
Wait, Finn.

08:46.526 --> 08:47.568
Please, stop it, man!

08:47.652 --> 08:49.945
We don't like touching each other.

08:50.030 --> 08:50.863
Huh?

08:50.947 --> 08:51.739
Please, man.

08:51.823 --> 08:52.948
Wait a second.

08:53.033 --> 08:54.283
Kim, get underneath Trudy.

08:54.367 --> 08:56.326
No, man. Please.

08:56.411 --> 08:58.579
l frickin' hate Trudy.

08:58.663 --> 09:00.873
Kim, l will destroy you!

09:00.957 --> 09:02.541
Okay, okay!

09:02.625 --> 09:03.625
[ chuckles ]

09:03.710 --> 09:05.586
Yeah, do it, Kim.

09:05.670 --> 09:06.503
[ stammers ]

09:06.588 --> 09:07.379
Yes!

09:07.464 --> 09:08.756
Now for me.

09:08.840 --> 09:09.757
[ grunts ]

09:09.841 --> 09:10.799
Look at us!

09:10.884 --> 09:13.302
Whoa!

09:13.386 --> 09:15.512
We're like a big, normal guy.

09:15.597 --> 09:17.056
Thank you so much.

09:17.140 --> 09:18.891
We're perfect together.

09:18.975 --> 09:20.184
Oh, Finn, thank you.

09:20.268 --> 09:21.101
Word!

09:21.186 --> 09:23.228
Now let's go wreck up that Magic Man!

09:23.313 --> 09:25.689
[ indistinct shouting ]

09:25.774 --> 09:27.399
Let me get in on this.

09:27.484 --> 09:28.817
l'll form the pants.

09:28.902 --> 09:30.611
Food. Food for a beggar.

09:30.695 --> 09:31.612
[ gasps ]

09:31.696 --> 09:32.780
Y'all got any food?

09:32.864 --> 09:34.239
We've got a little
orange juice left over from --

09:34.324 --> 09:37.034
Wait a second.

09:37.118 --> 09:37.910
That's right.

09:37.994 --> 09:39.495
lt is I, the Magic Man!

09:39.579 --> 09:40.370
Zap!

09:40.455 --> 09:41.288
[ all shout ]

09:41.372 --> 09:42.748
Come on, apple grease!

09:42.832 --> 09:44.583
What are you gonna do? Ohh!

09:44.667 --> 09:45.918
We're not afraid!

09:46.002 --> 09:48.545
Are you sureabout that?

09:48.630 --> 09:50.297
You're darn right we are!

09:50.381 --> 09:51.548
[ vomits ]

09:51.633 --> 09:52.424
Whoop!

09:52.509 --> 09:54.218
Give us our bodies back!

09:54.302 --> 09:55.677
[ shouts ]

09:55.762 --> 09:56.929
Why should l?

09:57.013 --> 10:00.265
You still act like a hero only so
youcan get what youwant.

10:00.350 --> 10:01.183
Oh.

10:01.267 --> 10:02.643
You were trying to teach us to

10:02.727 --> 10:05.020
be kind without expecting
anything in return.

10:05.105 --> 10:06.605
l should've given you that sugar

10:06.689 --> 10:09.066
cube without even thinking
about a reward.

10:09.150 --> 10:10.400
Wrong!

10:10.485 --> 10:11.318
Whoa! Whoa!

10:11.402 --> 10:12.903
Ah, geez! Finn!

10:12.987 --> 10:14.988
You've gifted us nothing
but heartache, Magic Man!

10:15.073 --> 10:16.323
What's the life lesson in that?!

10:16.407 --> 10:17.825
[ laughs maniacally ]

10:17.909 --> 10:22.079
Yes, my children,
you are so close to the answer.

10:22.163 --> 10:24.123
Answer This!

10:24.207 --> 10:25.791
Get his eyes!

10:25.875 --> 10:26.959
Cut him in the eyes!

10:27.043 --> 10:31.213
l wish l'd never been nice to you
'cause you're just a big jerk!

10:31.297 --> 10:32.965
Oh, yes, that's it!

10:33.049 --> 10:35.843
You've finally learned your lesson.

10:35.927 --> 10:41.056
And now l'm off to spread my
teachings to more sissy do-gooders.

10:41.141 --> 10:42.474
You're welcome!

10:42.559 --> 10:44.643
Man, l frickin' hate that guy.

10:44.727 --> 10:47.729
But at least now we can all
go back to our regular lives.

10:47.814 --> 10:48.856
Well, actually...

10:48.940 --> 10:50.315
We like being like this.

10:50.400 --> 10:51.984
Yeah, we're strong together.

10:52.068 --> 10:53.235
ALL:
Bye, Finn! Thank you!

10:53.319 --> 10:55.070
Oh, okay. Bye, guys.

